      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those symptoms like redness and slight warmth aren't uncommon in the initial stages of healing! The yellow ooze is likely normal discharge, helping to clear the site. While gentle cleaning is good, avoid harsh chemicals, but use a topical antibiotic cream from the chemist with the lid applied. If the warmth increases significantly or pain escalates over the next day, you should definitely call your doctor for a check-up.",
      "source": "target",
