      "content": "Apply the antibiotic cream as directed on the package, usually twice a day to keep the wound nourished and fighting bacteria. However, please do *not* use rubbing alcohol, as it is too harsh and actually irritates tissues slowing healing. Simply gently pat the area dry with sterile gauze before applying the prescribed topical medication. Trust the cream to maintain a clean barrier, not harsh spirits!",
